    "History": {
      "rows": [
        [
          "Staff Generated Concept",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "You keep everything in order - because that's how House and Clan prospers and grows.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Jenn Wolfe"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were born of a long line of magi, steeped in the Hermetic Order. The Munros were proud of where they came from and you followed in their footsteps. It shocked very few you joined House Tytalus when you took up your magical training and you had all the hallmarks of being the next great member of the family in the Order. But the world was Industrializing and magic was failing, and it didn't take an idiot to figure out that the Traditions, particularly not the Order of Hermes, didn't have an answer for it. All Tytalans knew of their lost siblings, House Tremere, the Massassa, the renegades who consorted with vampires. The Tytalans perhaps felt they were the masters of the Will, but it was the Tremere who actually used theirs and made themselves vampires, and not only that, but a clan of their own with magics of their own. Intrigued, you approached them directly, and they were only too happy to bring someone as promising as you across.\n\nYou have accepted the Code and Clan and have been a prominent rising start because of it. You are loyal to the vision of the clan, seeing in it the will to survive that the Tytalans have flirted with, but never grasped. The Traditions are losing the Ascension War and have no way of winning, but maybe the Tremere have found a loophole and a way of survival that will see through the dark times. Perhaps, with enough research and creativity, they can also move beyond the bounds of vampirism itself to return to what they were with a new kind of magic, a new kind of insight. It may sound foolish to some, but the Tremere are about survival, and you know that there are rumbles of things coming.\n\nYour steadfastness and commitment to the Tremere vision has allowed you to rise at a steady pace, moving from one problem chantry to another and aiding their regents into bringing them into line. Your appointment to Los Angeles in many ways is a foregone conclusion, you've just been waiting for a chantry to call your own. Los Angeles, from all you've heard, hasn't exactly been a poorly run chantry, despite the exit of Dafne Pictor. Both she and Villalobos were traditionalists who worked closely with the Justicar and built a good foundation for the Tremere in the domain, there is a lot sound structure here. But, Los Angeles is in former Anarch territory, and they do have a presence, many with their own bastardized forms of blood magic. And then there is this House Carna business, the rumors you've heard of disgruntled factions attempting to break off and form their own way. There are far more important things in this world than personal freedom, you know that better than anyone, and the stakes are too high to be undisciplined."
        ],
